The paper deals with deep neural networks and their performance in image classification tasks, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a modification to off-the-shelf DNNs, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the computational efficiency of DNNs, which is related to neural networks (cs.NE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.CR.
